open Vivado
open project "student_P2"
add simulation file "tb_top.v"
copy/type the lines below into "tb_top.v":

`timescale 1ns / 1ps

module tb_top();

    reg a = 1'b0; // register for half adder inputs
    reg b = 1'b0; // register for half adder inputs

    wire sum;
    wire carry;

    top UUT (.A(a),.B(b),.SUM(sum),.CARRY(carry));

    initial begin
    a = 0;
    b = 0;
    #1000

    a = 0;
    b = 1;
    #1000

// add code here

    a = 1;
    b = 1;
    #1000
    $display("test complete");
end

endmodule

click "run simulation in vivado"
observe a,b toggle
observe sum, carry toggle

questions:
1) What does #1000 represent?
2) Can you add code to check condition where a = 1 and b = 0?
